Interface TreeTraverseListener

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    MTree, Tree

    public interface TreeTraverseListener
    Interface that is used by the TreeTraverser class to call back when a node is being traversed.
    Author:
    Pat B. Double (double@i2rd.com)

        void nodeTraversed(Tree tree,
                 TreePath path,
                 int row,
                 Object traverseInfo,
                 boolean hadSibilingPreceeding,
                 boolean hasSiblingFollowing)
        Indicates a node is being traversed.
        Parameters:
        tree - The tree component.
        path - The path to the node.
        row - The row.
        traverseInfo - An object passed into the traverse method of the TreeTraverser object.
        hadSibilingPreceeding - true if the path had a sibiling preceeding.
        hasSiblingFollowing - true if the path has a sibiling following.
